  <!-- Intro -->
  <p class="section-label">WHAT IS THIS</p>
  <div class="intro">
    <p>NECROBIOME is a <span class="hi">cyberpunk Conway's Game of Life simulator</span> where every cell is a unique creature with its own genome, diet, energy, memories, and ambitions.</p>
    <p>They are born. They eat. They build. They hunt. They grow old. They die. Some of them learn. Some evolve into something you've never seen before.</p>
    <p>You didn't design them. You can't fully control them. You can only <span class="hi2">watch, intervene, and wonder.</span></p>
  </div>

  <!-- Biomes -->
  <p class="section-label">THE BIOMES</p>
  <div class="biome-grid">
    <div class="biome-card void">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#00FFB4">@ &nbsp; THE VOID</p>
      <p class="biome-desc">Deep emptiness that rewards loners. Background radiation feeds those who need no one. Social creatures starve here.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="biome-card neon">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#FF3296">! &nbsp; NEON WASTES</p>
      <p class="biome-desc">Carnivore country. Neon fungi feed only the aggressive. Passive creatures starve. The highest carnivore density in any biome.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="biome-card reef">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#00C8FF">~ &nbsp; DATA REEF</p>
      <p class="biome-desc">Data plankton feeds social creatures. Long lineages earn bonus energy. The Reef remembers who has always been here.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="biome-card chrome">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#C8C8C8">- &nbsp; CHROME FLATS</p>
      <p class="biome-desc">The quietest place. Chrome moss rewards patience. Old creatures live longest here. Slow metabolizers accumulate energy over time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="biome-card acid">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#64FF00">% &nbsp; ACID DELTA</p>
      <p class="biome-desc">Dangerous and alive. Acid Floods kill the weak and feed the resilient. Survivors are changed. Their children inherit the strength.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="biome-card cyber">
      <p class="biome-name" style="color:#CC00FF">ОЁ &nbsp; PERSONAL CYBERSPACE</p>
      <p class="biome-desc" style="color:#441166">Hidden. Unlocked through deep evolution. The Conway rules rewrite themselves every 60 ticks. Only the deeply adapted survive.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Systems -->
  <p class="section-label">CORE SYSTEMS</p>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="systems-grid">
      <div class="system-item">
        <h3>Genome</h3>
        <p>16-character DNA strings encoding diet, metabolism, aggression, resilience, sociability. Copy any creature's genome, paste it anywhere, or write your own from scratch.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="system-item">
        <h3>Evolution</h3>
        <p>Creatures remember which neighbor counts kept them alive. Mutations are guided by memory, not pure chance. Lineages develop genuine specialisation over generations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="system-item">
        <h3>Structures</h3>
        <p>Social creatures place blueprints. Family members contribute materials toward the cost. When funded, it constructs automatically. Void Anchors. Neon Spires. Data Nodes. Homes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="system-item">
        <h3>Day &amp; Night</h3>
        <p>A 300-tick cycle. Diurnal creatures gain bonus energy in daylight. Nocturnal ones thrive in the dark. Carnivores get a 1.5Г— hunt bonus at night.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

